The UltraFLEXplus and UltraFLEX use the award-winning IG-XL software from Teradyne for test program development. This software provides a robust graphical environment, making it easier to develop and debug programs. It even allows automatic conversion of single site test programs to multisite, which can save significant development time. One of the strengths of this software is that you do not need to write code specifically for the tester, which suggests that you don't need a particular programming language to debug the UltraFLEXplus. 

However, should you require a particular language support, it's worth noting that the Teradyne website has support for English, Chinese Simplified, Japanese, and Korean, which may imply some level of language support within the IG-XL software itself.
